.TH NIRIBAR 1 "2026-07-02" "niribar 0.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
niribar \- an i3bar status-protocol bar for niri
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B niribar
.RB [ \-d ]
.RB [ \-s
.IR socket ]
.RB [ \-f
.IR config ]
.RB [ \-b
.IR bar-id ]
.RB [ \-c
.IR command ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B niribar
draws a workspace and status bar for the niri compositor.
It uses swaybar's Wayland renderer and understands the i3bar status protocol,
while workspace state and actions come from niri's IPC socket.
.PP
Run niribar inside an existing niri session.  With no configuration file it
uses the familiar swaybar defaults: a bar at the bottom, workspace buttons on
the left, and no status command.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a short usage message and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print the version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-debug
Enable debug logging.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-socket " " \fIsocket\fR
Connect to this niri IPC socket instead of
.BR NIRI_SOCKET .
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-config " " \fIconfig\fR
Read bar configuration from
.IR config .
This takes precedence over the normal search path.
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-bar-id " " \fIbar-id\fR
Select the named
.B bar
block when the configuration contains more than one.  Without this option,
the first block is used.  In a named block, place
.B id
before the settings that belong to it.
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-status-command " " \fIcommand\fR
Run
.I command
through
.BR sh (1)
and show its output on the right.  This overrides
.B status_command
from the configuration file.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration parser accepts a subset of i3
.B bar
block syntax:
.PP
.EX
bar {
    position top
    font pango:DejaVu Sans Mono 10
    status_command i3status

    colors {
        background #000000
        statusline #ffffff
        focused_workspace #4c7899 #285577 #ffffff
    }
}
.EE
.PP
niribar looks for a configuration in this order:
.IP 1. 3
The path passed with
.BR \-\-config .
.IP 2. 3
.BR NIRIBAR_CONFIG .
.IP 3. 3
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/niribar/config .
.IP 4. 3
.IR ~/.config/niribar/config .
.IP 5. 3
.IR ~/.niribarrc .
.IP 6. 3
.IR /etc/xdg/niribar/config .
.PP
The following settings are applied:
.BR status_command ,
.BR mode ,
.BR hidden_state ,
.BR position ,
.BR output ,
.BR font ,
.BR separator_symbol ,
.BR workspace_buttons ,
.BR workspace_min_width ,
.BR strip_workspace_numbers ,
.BR strip_workspace_name ,
.BR binding_mode_indicator ,
.BR bindsym ,
.BR height ,
and
.BR colors .
.PP
An
.B output
value must be an exact niri output name; i3's
.B primary
and
.B nonprimary
aliases have no special meaning.  The
.B padding
directive is accepted, but currently sets layer-surface margins rather than
i3bar content padding.
.PP
For mouse bindings,
.B nop
is ignored and the i3
.B exec
prefix is stripped.  The remaining command is run by
.BR sh (1).
.PP
For source-file compatibility,
.BR i3bar_command ,
.BR workspace_command ,
.BR tray_output ,
.BR tray_padding ,
and
.B modifier
are accepted but have no effect.  niribar does not provide a system tray.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B NIRI_SOCKET
Path to niri's IPC socket.  Set automatically by niri.
.TP
.B NIRIBAR_CONFIG
Configuration path used when
.B \-\-config
is not given.
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for per-user configuration.  If unset,
.I ~/.config
is checked directly.
.TP
.B HOME
Used for the fallback configuration paths.
.SH EXAMPLES
Start with the first configured bar:
.PP
.EX
niribar
.EE
.PP
Use a particular bar block and status command:
.PP
.EX
niribar --config ~/.config/niribar/config --bar-id laptop
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR niri (1),
.BR i3status (1),
.BR swaybar-protocol (7)
